OL,3,CShould the Channel Islands give carers
OL,4,Cunpaid leave?
OL,6,FUp to 6,000 people in could benefit
OL,7,Ffrom unpaid carer leave if the Channel
OL,8,FIslands follows the UK in introducing
OL,9,Fa new scheme.
OL,11,FThe British Government now allows
OL,12,Fcarers five days of unpaid leave each
OL,13,Fyear after many compared their
OL,14,Flifestyle to having two full-time jobs.
OL,16,FOne islander in Guernsey who cares for
OL,17,Fher mother says if officials there
OL,18,Ffollowed suit, it would relieve
OL,19,Fstress: "It would be very good, I
OL,20,Fthink as carers you can plan it well.
