OL,3,CShould the Channel Islands give carers
OL,4,Cunpaid leave?
OL,6,FLyndsay Feltham, Jersey's Social
OL,7,FSecurity Minister, says: "I'd be keen
OL,8,Fto look at carers leave, together with
OL,9,Fwhere we fall with statutory sick
OL,10,Fleave and other areas where we may
OL,11,Fwell be falling behind."
OL,13,FHowever, Deputy Linsday de Sausmarez,
OL,14,FVice President of Guernsey's
OL,15,FEmployment and Social Security
OL,16,FCommittee, says: "The Committee hasn't
OL,17,Fdiscussed the idea previously, and
OL,18,Fwhilst I am sympathetic to it, it
OL,19,Fcannot be investigated in this
OL,20,FAssembly as it's not one of the
OL,21,Fapproved workstreams under the GWP."
